        "This feast celebrates not only the physical building but the spiritual significance of honoring Mary as Mother of God. The basilica stands as a testament to the Church's ancient and continuous devotion to Mary and serves as a mother church for all Marian shrines throughout the world. The feast invites the faithful to renew their devotion to Mary and to recognize her unique role in salvation history.",
