        "The theological foundation for Mary's queenship is found in Scripture and tradition. In the Old Testament, the Queen Mother (Hebrew: Gebirah) held an important position in the Davidic kingdom, sitting at the king's right hand and serving as intercessor for the people. Mary fulfills this role perfectly as the Mother of Jesus, the eternal King from the line of David.",
