        "The Lateran Basilica served as the papal residence and the center of Church administration for nearly a thousand years, from the 4th to the 14th centuries, until the papacy moved to Avignon and later to the Vatican. Even today, the Pope's cathedra (bishop's throne) is in the Lateran, not St. Peter's Basilica, making it his cathedral church.",
